   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building capacity for inclusive service delivery</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Ministry of Welfare and Social Security (MoWSS) is implementing the &quot;BUILDING CAPACITY FOR INCLUSIVE SERVICE DELIVERY&quot; project in partnership with the African Development Bank. The project is managed by a Programme Implementation Unit established inside the Ministry. The ILO will take responsibility under the AfDB-MoWSS programme for the realisation of the programme&apos;s third outcome: Sustainable community-based safety-net platforms in North Kordofan and White Nile. These include the following activities: -Develop a Gender Sensitive Safety Net Framework and innovative solutions -Carry out and conduct a skills profiling and assess training needs for target population -Design a tailored training program suiting the skills profile -Develop implementation and financing plans for skills utilization for groups and individuals -Create Enabling Business Environment for the trained to practice skills and earn income</narrative>
  </description>
